description:
The city of Corinth sits in a beautiful location overlooking the sea and during Paul’s ministry he visited it twice. Adopting a different strategy than he had in Athens, Paul unashamedly preached the gospel of Christ without apology. Here in Corinth Paul stayed for 18 months and whilst ministering there he supported himself as a tentmaker showing his adaptability and industriousness.
